==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Escharotic
<hw>Es`cha*rot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ an eschar: cf. F. <ets>escharotique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Serving or tending to form an eschar; producing a scar;
caustic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Escharotic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Escharotic
<hw>Es`cha*rot"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A substance
which produces an eschar; a caustic, esp., a mild caustic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eschatological</ent>⟦br⟧
